iPhone App Proxy:

This works on a mac:
- Download Charles. http://www.charlesproxy.com/
- Setup HTTP Proxy in Charles. (Not SOCKS)
- On your iPhone, go to the WiFi settings, set the Proxy.
- Check this: http://www.charlesproxy.com/documentation/faqs/ssl-connections-from-within-iphone-applications/
	-> Download the certificates.
- Now open some random website from within Safari. Make sure Charles is
	is logging this traffic. If it's not, check your proxy settings.
- Open the SBB Application, do some requests. If not request to sbb.ch
	shows up: Try the "Reload" button in the connection list. Or the
	"Next" button.
